What is Scratch?

Scratch is a free programming language where you create games, animations, and stories by snapping together colorful blocks - just like LEGO! No typing required!

What You'll Learn

  • How to create a Scratch account
  • Understanding the Scratch interface
  • Your first "Hello World" project

Let's Get Started!

Step 1: Create Your Scratch Account

  1. Go to scratch.mit.edu
  2. Click "Join Scratch" in the top right
  3. Choose a username (make it fun!)
  4. Create a strong password
  5. Add your parent's email
  6. Click "Create Your Account"

Step 2: Explore the Scratch Interface

Once you're logged in, click "Create" to start a new project. You'll see:

  • Stage: Where your project comes to life (the white area)
  • Sprite: The cat you see (characters in your project)
  • Blocks Palette: All the coding blocks (left side)
  • Code Area: Where you drag blocks (middle)

Step 3: Make the Cat Say "Hello!"

  1. Look at the Blocks Palette on the left
  2. Click on "Looks" (purple blocks)
  3. Drag the "say Hello! for 2 seconds" block to the Code Area
  4. Click on the block and watch the cat!

Congratulations! You just wrote your first code!
